==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tentative
<hw>Ten*ta"tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tentare</ets> to try: cf. F. <ets>tentatif</ets>. See
<er>Tempt</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to a trial or trials;
essaying; experimental.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A slow, <xex>tentative</xex>
manner.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Carlyle.</au> -- <wordforms><wf>Ten*ta"tive*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tentative</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tentative
<hw>Ten*ta"tive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>tentative</ets>.]</ety> <def>An essay; a trial; an
experiment.</def> <rj><au>Berkley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tented</ent>⟦br⟧
